Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.02,1:05:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不 很舒适\N{\rE}- No. - It's cozy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.19,1:05:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是说房子我是说...\N{\rE}I don't mean the house. I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.55,1:05:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我有自己的想法\N{\rE}I have my own ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.89,1:05:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,也许你我都有这样的想法\N{\rE}Maybe you and I share some of those ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.50,1:05:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们分享什么样的想法？\N{\rE}What kind of ideas do we share?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.47,1:05:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我能向你倾诉吗\N{\rE}May I confide in you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.37,1:06:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\rE}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.51,1:06:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,是关于李·波尔克的\N{\rE}It's about Lee Polk.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.98,1:06:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是这样吗  - 是的\N{\rE}- It is? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.05,1:06:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我 亲爱的...\N{\rE}Tell me, honey...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.92,1:06:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,是什么让一个人想要杀死自己的父亲？\N{\rE}what would make a person want to kill their father?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.99,1:06:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都想杀死自己的父亲\N{\rE}Everybody wants to kill their father.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.26,1:06:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,不 他们没有 谁告诉你的？\N{\rE}No, they don't. Who told you that?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.76,1:06:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,真的 好好想想吧 艾琳\N{\rE}Really, think about it, Eileen.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.56,1:06:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,因为李偷偷溜进了父母的卧室\N{\rE}Because Lee snuck into his parents' bedroom
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.77,1:06:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,在半夜...\N{\rE}in the middle of the night...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.24,1:06:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,砍断了他父亲的喉咙\N{\rE}hacked through his father's throat
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.01,1:06:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,用一把旧菜刀\N{\rE}with an old kitchen knife,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.47,1:06:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,并多次刺中他的胸部\N{\rE}and stabbed him in the chest repeatedly.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.15,1:06:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他的母亲声称 她以为有人闯入\N{\rE}His mother claimed she thought there'd been a break-in.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.31,1:06:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你是怎么睡过去的？\N{\rE}How do you sleep through something like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.02,1:06:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rE}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.45,1:06:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你不知道所以我才叫她来\N{\rE}You don't. That's why I called her in.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.65,1:06:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 你当时在场\N{\rE}I mean, you were there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.16,1:06:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这个可怜的孩子几乎不敢看她 所以...\N{\rE}The poor boy could barely look at her, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.79,1:06:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,所以事后 我就直截了当地问他\N{\rE}so afterwards, I just asked him point-blank.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.66,1:06:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我说...\N{\rE}I said...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.43,1:06:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我说："你父亲对你做了什么？"\N{\rE}I said, "What'd your father do to you?"
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.04,1:07:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"是什么让你想这样对待你父亲的尸体？"\N{\rE}"What made you want to do that to your father's body?"
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.11,1:07:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他在短短几分钟内就全说了出来\N{\rE}And he spilled it all in a matter of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.51,1:07:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,以前从没人问过他\N{\rE}Nobody had ever bothered to ask him before.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.35,1:07:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人想过要问\N{\rE}No one had thought to ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.61,1:07:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你不想知道吗\N{\rE}Wouldn't you want to know?
